I%20pass%20away.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EI%20want%20my%20daughter%20to%20be%20protected%20if%20that%20happens%2C%20so%20I'm%20getting%20a%20will%20this%20year.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EI%20talked%20to%20a%20financial%20planner%20who%20told%20me%20how%20to%20inventory%20everything%20I%20have.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20I%20had%20my%20first%20child%20in%202023%2C%20a%20good%20friend%20of%20mine%20suggested%20that%20I%20get%20a%20will.%20She%20was%20a%20mom%20of%20three%20and%20stressed%20how%20important%20the%20legal%20document%20was%20not%20only%20to%20protect%20my%20assets%20but%20to%20have%20a%20plan%20laid%20out%20for%20my%20daughter%2C%20in%20case%20something%20were%20to%20happen%20to%20my%20partner%20or%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20I%20laughed%20at%20her%20advice.%20I%20thought%20it%20wasn't%20worthwhile%20to%20invest%20in%20an%20estate%20plan%20if%20I%20didn't%20have%20any%20assets.%20I%20don't%20own%20real%20estate%20or%20a%20car%2C%20and%20I%20don't%20have%20an%20inheritance%20fund.%20But%20whenever%20I%20thought%20about%20my%20daughter%20and%20how%20to%20set%20her%20up%20for%20financial%20success%2C%20the%20idea%20of%20having%20a%20will%20in%20place%20kept%20coming%20up.%20If%20I%20were%20to%20pass%20away%2C%20a%20will%20would%20direct%20the%20distribution%20of%20any%20assets%20that%20I%20do%20have%20and%20make%20the%20process%20easier%20on%20her%2C%20making%20it%20essential%20to%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Ffinancial-planning%5C%22%3Efinancial%20planning%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20learn%20more%20about%20the%20process%2C%20I%20spoke%20to%20estate%20planning%20attorney%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dgimlaw.com%2Fteam%2Fmonique-d-hayes%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMonique%20Hayes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20asked%20her%20to%20explain%20why%20it%20would%20be%20beneficial%20for%20a%20person%20like%20myself%20to%20get%20a%20will%2C%20even%20though%20I%20don't%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20traditional%20assets.%20I%20started%20off%20by%20sharing%20important%20details%20about%20myself%20with%20her.%20I%20told%20her%20that%20I'm%2035%20and%20married%20with%20one%20child%20under%20the%20age%20of%201.%20I%20am%20the%20sole%20owner%20of%20a%20business%2C%20a%20published%20author%2C%20and%20a%20content%20creator.%20After%20learning%20more%20about%20me%2C%20here's%20what%20Hayes%20shared.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EIt's%20important%20to%20have%20a%20plan%20in%20place%20for%20kids%20under%20the%20age%20of%2018%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20biggest%20reasons%20I%20was%20interested%20in%20getting%20a%20will%20this%20year%20was%20that%20my%20daughter%20is%20almost%201%2C%20and%20if%20something%20were%20to%20happen%20to%20my%20husband%20and%20me%2C%20there%20needs%20to%20be%20a%20plan%20in%20place%20for%20her%20physical%20and%20financial%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHayes%20said%20that%20once%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20agree%20on%20who%20will%20have%20guardianship%20of%20her%2C%20we%20need%20to%20list%20that%20in%20a%20will.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20don't%20document%20that%20in%20a%20will%2C%20or%20other%20recognized%20designation%20record%2C%20your%20preference%20for%20who%20will%20have%20guardianship%20over%20her%20will%20be%20unknown%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20will%20be%20left%20up%20to%20a%20court%20to%20decide%20who%20is%20the%20best%20person%20in%20your%20family%2C%20or%20friend%20group%2C%C2%A0%20to%20raise%20her.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it's%20tough%20to%20think%20about%20the%20scenario%20that%20she%20would%20grow%20up%20without%20my%20husband%20or%20me%20being%20here%2C%20if%20something%20were%20to%20happen%20to%20us%2C%20I%20don't%20want%20any%20burdens%20to%20fall%20on%20her%20or%20any%20disputes%20to%20arise%20among%20our%20loved%20ones%20about%20her%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EIntellectual%20property%20is%20an%20asset%20that%20can%20generate%20wealth%20in%20the%20future%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20narrow-mindedly%20assumed%20that%20assets%20were%20only%20related%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-real-estate-investing-platforms%5C%22%3Ereal%20estate%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20cars%2C%20and%20other%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-are-the-best-investment-apps%5C%22%3Einvestment%3C%2Fa%3E%20opportunities.%20But%20Hayes%20quickly%20reminded%20me%20that%20my%20books%20count%20as%20valuable%20assets%20that%20can%20grow%20in%20value%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIntellectual%20property%20is%20defined%20to%20include%20a%20broad%20category%20of%20intangible%20assets%20that%20may%20be%20owned.%20In%20the%20United%20States%2C%20the%20primary%20intellectual%20property%20categories%20are%20patents%2C%20trademarks%2C%20copyrights%2C%20and%20trade%20secrets.%20In%20simple%20terms%2C%20it's%20your%20ideas%20and%20the%20content%20you%20create%20from%20those%20ideas.%20Your%20published%20books%20absolutely%20count%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20shared.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20always%20a%20chance%20down%20the%20road%20that%20someone%20wants%20to%20option%20those%20stories%20and%20turn%20them%20into%20movies%2C%20films%2C%20or%20other%20mediums%20in%20the%20future.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHayes%20stressed%20that%20it's%20important%20to%20protect%20and%20preserve%20that%20intellectual%20property%2C%20especially%20in%20your%20will.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20don't%2C%20then%20it%20could%20open%20up%20the%20door%20for%20disputes%20within%20your%20family%2C%20third-party%20leveraging%2C%20or%20manipulation.%20Rather%20than%20have%20it%20end%20up%20in%20probate%2C%20list%20in%20your%20will%20who%20you%20want%20to%20own%20your%20intellectual%20property%20once%20you%20pass%20away.%20You%20can%20also%20detail%20the%20uses%20of%20your%20intellectual%20property%20that%20are%20allowed%20in%20the%20future.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20your%20family%20might%20not%20know%20the%20full%20extent%20of%20your%20intellectual%20property%2C%20Hayes%20recommended%20making%20a%20list%20of%20any%20intellectual%20property%20you%20might%20have.%20If%20you're%20not%20sure%2C%20Hayes%20suggested%20taking%20the%20time%20to%20prepare%20an%20inventory%20of%20everything%20you%20have%20created%20in%20your%20business%20and%20professional%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDocument%20those%20things%2C%20and%20then%20decide%20who%20you%20would%20want%20to%20have%20them%2C%20and%20record%20that%20in%20a%20will%20or%20other%20estate%20plan%20document%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20it%20may%20just%20be%20a%20manuscript%20today%2C%20but%20that%20manuscript%2020%20years%20from%20now%20may%20be%20a%20blockbuster.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EDigital%20assets%20might%20be%20meaningful%20and%20important%20to%20loved%20ones%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20a%20content%20creator%20who%20shares%20a%20lot%20of%20my%20life%20on%20social%20media%2C%20inside%20a%20newsletter%2C%20and%20on%20my%20personal%20website.%20Hayes%20reminded%20me%20that%20these%20items%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20my%20email%20inbox%2C%20are%20digital%20assets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEveryone%20in%20today's%20world%20has%20digital%20assets%2C%26quot%3B%20Hayes%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20pass%20away%2C%20you%20want%20to%20have%20a%20plan%20for%20who%20will%20be%20able%20to%20access%20your%20email%2C%20social%20media%20accounts%2C%20and%20even%20your%20smartphone%2C%20with%20all%20the%20cloud-based%20data.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20don't%20have%20this%20listed%20in%20your%20will%20or%20estate%20plan%2C%20Hayes%20said%20your%20family%20might%20have%20to%20enter%20a%20costly%20and%20time-consuming%20probate%20process%20just%20to%20be%20able%20to%20access%20those%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWithout%20a%20will%20that%20declares%20who%20would%20control%20your%20digital%20assets%2C%20the%20only%20way%20your%20family%20would%20be%20able%20to%20access%20these%20accounts%20is%20by%20going%20through%20a%20costly%20and%20time-consuming%20probate%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20shared.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20business%20needs%20a%20succession%20plan%2C%20especially%20if%20you're%20the%20sole%20owner%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHayes%20reminded%20me%20that%20as%20the%20sole%20owner%20of%20my%20business%2C%20that's%20an%20asset%20that%20I%20need%20to%20plan%20for%20in%20my%20will%20in%20case%20something%20happens%20to%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20don't%20have%20a%20beneficiary%20designated%2C%20it%20would%20be%20left%20up%20to%20the%20court%20to%20decide%20who%20would%20have%20ownership%20of%20your%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BProbate%20proceedings%20can%20take%20years%2C%20which%20is%20problematic%20for%20a%20business%20that's%20alive%20and%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20my%20business%20is%20functioning%20and%20there%20are%20pieces%20that%20need%20someone%20to%20preside%20over%2C%20from%20paying%20vendors%20to%20handling%20clients%2C%20the%20court%20might%20appoint%20a%20professional%20fiduciary%20to%20run%20the%20business%20while%20ownership%20is%20determined.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20could%20be%20disruptive%20to%20the%20business%20operations%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20never%20thought%20of%20this%20before%20and%20realized%20if%20I%20don't%20have%20a%20succession%20plan%20outlined%20in%20my%20will%2C%20my%20business%20might%20completely%20unravel%20before%20someone%20is%20appointed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EPeople%20have%20more%20assets%20than%20they%20think%20they%20do%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20briefly%20sharing%20my%20personal%20background%20with%20Hayes%2C%20she%20was%20able%20to%20help%20me%20see%20that%20I%20have%20more%20assets%20than%20I%20ever%20thought%20I%20did.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWealth%20is%20more%20than%20just%20the%20dollars%20and%20cents%20you%20have%20access%20to%20today.%20It's%20the%20physical%20and%20intangible%20assets%20that%20can%20be%20monetized%20in%20the%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20also%20the%20values%2C%20work%20ethic%2C%20resources%20that%20can%20sustain%20a%20family%20across%20generations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20spent%20an%20afternoon%20taking%20inventory%20of%20what%20I%20own%20and%20came%20up%20with%20a%20list%20of%20things%20that%20would%20need%20to%20be%20listed%20in%20my%20will.%20I%20included%20things%20like%20my%20diamond%20engagement%20ring%2C%20stowed%20cash%2C%20my%20beloved%20dog%2C%20and%20other%20personal%20items%2C%20from%20antiques%20to%20expensive%20furniture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20like%20with%20any%20other%20asset%2C%20without%20a%20will%2C%20these%20items%20would%20be%20left%20up%20to%20the%20court's%20decision%20on%20how%20they%20should%20be%20divided.%20That's%20not%20what%20I%20want%2C%20and%20I%20certainly%20don't%20want%20to%20put%20the%20burden%20on%20my%20daughter%2C%20or%20family%20members%2C%20to%20get%20that%20sorted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20I%20didn't%20think%20I%20needed%20a%20will%2C%20I%20realized%20that%20it's%20on%20the%20top%20of%20my%20to-do%20list%20for%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhow-to-find-financial-advisor%5C%22%3EFinding%20a%20qualified%20financial%20advisor%3C%2Fa%3E%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20hard.%20SmartAsset's%20free%20tool%20matches%20you%20with%20up%20to%20three%20fiduciary%20financial%20advisors%20in%20your%20area%20in%20minutes.%20Each%20advisor%20has%20been%20vetted%20by%20SmartAdvisor%20and%20is%20held%20to%20a%20fiduciary%20standard%20to%20act%20in%20your%20best%20interests.%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartasset.com%2Fretirement%2Ffind-a-financial-planner%3Futm_source%3Dbusinessinsider%26utm_medium%3Dcpc%26utm_campaign%3Dbus__falc_bicontent%26utm_content%3DBI%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Start%20your%20search%20now.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20art