n%20X-Ray%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20Compassion%20Reveal%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F13162917%2Fsonika-agarwal-XCJkr6Is0B8-unsplash1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20recent%20incidents%20provide%20a%20rubric%20for%20us%20to%20evaluate%20our%20priorities%20and%20imaginations%20of%20India.%20The%20first%20is%20the%20extraordinary%20heroic%20effort%20in%20which%2012%20rat-hole%20miners%20rescued%2041%20daily%20wage%20workers%20who%20were%20trapped%20in%20the%20Silkyara%20tunnel%20in%20Uttarakhand%20for%20over%2016%20days.%20The%20second%20incident%20concerns%20a%20statement%20in%20the%20Parliament.%20On%2021%20September%2C%20Ramesh%20Bidhuri%2C%20a%20Member%20of%20Parliament%20(MP)%20of%20the%20BJP%20made%20derogatory%20communal%20slurs%20against%20Danish%20Ali%20of%20the%20BSP%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20the%20parliament.%20The%20comments%20received%20applause%20from%20some%20BJP%20MPs%20in%20the%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20incidents%20are%20seemingly%20unrelated.%20The%20thread%20that%20connects%20the%20two%20is%20the%20continued%20acceptance%20of%20precarity%2C%20indignity%20and%20discrimination%20faced%20by%20many%20in%20our%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Silkyara%20tunnel%20is%20part%20of%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20much%20publicised%20Char%20Dham%20project%20to%20build%20roads%20connecting%20the%20four%20Hindu%20pilgrimage%20sites%20of%20Kedarnath%2C%20Badrinath%2C%20Gangotri%2C%20and%20Yamunotri.%20While%20building%20roads%20are%20required%2C%20what%20needs%20interrogation%20is%20the%20rush%20to%20complete%20projects%20by%20ignoring%20environmental%20concerns%20and%20safeguards%20that%20puts%20socio-economically%20poor%20workers%20at%20the%20fulcrum%20of%20life%20and%20death.%20And%2C%20when%20a%20sitting%20MP%20gets%20away%20with%20derogatory%20speech%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20Parliament%2C%20it%20deifies%20resentment%2C%20legitimises%20prejudice%20and%20creates%20precedents%20for%20disharmony.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETogether%2C%20these%20incidents%20demonstrate%20the%20need%20to%20pay%20attention%20to%20how%20the%20constitutional%20promises%20of%20dignity%2C%20equality%20and%20fraternity%20are%20playing%20out%20in%20practice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20stands%20at%20the%20cusp%20of%20a%20historically%20tenuous%20time.%20Its%20economic%20structures%20have%20systematically%20fortified%20a%20class%20of%20people%20and%20rendered%20the%20poor%20to%20lead%20a%20fractured%20existence%20in%20the%20penumbra%20of%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Fopinion%2Finternet-in-the-time-of-floods-2805109%5C%22%3Egated%20lives%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bottom%20half%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20population%20holds%20a%20mere%203%25%20of%20the%20national%20wealth.%20When%20seen%20from%20this%20economic%20axis%2C%20it%20is%20the%20poor%20that%20constitute%20the%20numerical%20majority.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESplicing%20India%20along%20a%20religious%20axis%20creates%20a%20majoritarian%20idiom%20which%20is%20different%20from%20the%20absolute%20numerical%20majority%20comprising%20the%20poor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20majority%20is%20just%20one%20economic%20or%20health%20shock%20away%20from%20slipping%20into%20utter%20destitution.%20Inadequate%20social%20safety%20nets%20and%20the%20daily%20grind%20have%20trapped%20the%20poor%20in%20a%20Sisyphean%20cycle%20of%20precarity.%20Inter-generational%20mobility%20towards%20economic%20prosperity%20has%20been%20sluggish%20pointing%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theindiaforum.in%2Feconomy%2Fgrowth-structural-change-and-opportunities-who-has-benefited%5C%22%3Econtinuance%20of%20deprivation%20along%20caste%20lines%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20economically%20poor%20are%20over-represented%20by%20socially%20marginalised%20communities%20such%20as%20Dalits%20and%20Adivasis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20parallel%20to%20this%20economic%20disrepair%2C%20a%20continuous%20injection%20of%20resentment%20incites%20decentralised%20and%20splintered%20acts%20of%20discrimination%20and%20violence%20targeting%20Muslims.%20The%20tacit%20sanction%20from%20the%20government%20of%20such%20acts%20makes%20the%20force%20of%20law%20indistinguishable%20from%20the%20law%20of%20force%20(Hansen%202021).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20collateral%20damage%20of%20such%20politics%20of%20precarity%20and%20politics%20of%20prejudice%20is%20a%20steady%20erosion%20and%20corrosion%20of%20compassion.%20Erosion%20is%20a%20gradual%2C%20structurally%20mediated%20physical%20process%20while%20corrosion%20is%20akin%20to%20a%20biochemically%20induced%20process%20with%20lasting%20and%20even%20irreversible%20implications.%20The%20politics%20of%20precarity%20and%20heightened%20socio-economic%20inequality%20erodes%20our%20compassion%3B%20the%20politics%20of%20prejudice%20and%20the%20treatment%20of%20minorities%20corrodes%20it.%20These%20raise%20the%20question%3A%20what%20would%20an%20X-Ray%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20compassion%20reveal%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fbecause-hes-muslim-asks-wife-of-uttarkashi-tunnel-rescuer-whose-house-was-demolished%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Because%20He%E2%80%99s%20Muslim%3F%E2%80%99%20Asks%20Wife%20of%20Uttarkashi%20Tunnel%20Rescuer%20Whose%20House%20Was%20Demolished%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20eroding%20state%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20last%20decade%2C%20we%20observe%20a%20steady%20reconfiguration%20of%20the%20citizen-state%20relationship.%20This%20is%20an%20inversion%20from%20the%20time%20between%202004%20and%202013%20when%20a%20set%20of%20rights-based%20legislations%20such%20as%20NREGA%2C%20NFSA%2C%20and%20the%20Forest%20Rights%20Act%2C%20were%20imagined%20as%20attempts%20to%20improve%20participatory%20democracy%20and%20the%20bargaining%20power%20of%20the%20marginalised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theindiaforum.in%2Fpublic-policy%2Fcitizen-vs-labharthi%5C%22%3Estate%20steadily%20abdicates%20%3C%2Fa%3Eits%20responsibility%20of%20enabling%20citizens%E2%80%99%20rights.%20It%20puts%20the%20onus%20on%20the%20citizen%2C%20as%20if%20it%20is%20the%20citizen%E2%80%99s%20fault%20and%20not%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20responsibility%20to%20honour%20rights.%20For%20instance%2C%20not%20being%20able%20to%20get%20pensions%20owing%20to%20biometric%20or%20other%20technical%20failures%20is%20now%20framed%20as%20a%20citizen%E2%80%99s%20fault%20instead%20of%20seeing%20it%20as%20a%20fault%20with%20the%20design%20and%20principles%20of%20governance.%20The%20patronising%20language%20of%20terming%20individuals%20as%20%E2%80%98beneficiaries%E2%80%99%20instead%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fopinion%2Fop-ed%2Fthe-efficiency-myth-of-aadhaar-linking%2Farticle38067084.ece%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98rights-holders%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%20brands%20and%20repackages%20the%20government%20as%20a%20philanthropic%20institution%20doling%20out%20charity%20and%20further%20strips%20the%20citizen%20of%20her%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAided%20by%20digital%20technologies%2C%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%20rights-based%20legislations%20have%20become%20excessively%20centralised%20leading%20to%20a%20flattening%20of%20federalism%20and%20routine%20violations%20of%20rights%20(Buddha%2C%20Dhorajiwala%20and%20Narayanan%2C%202021)%2C%20(Chaudhuri%2C%20B%202020)%2C%20(Dr%C3%A8ze%2C%20Jean%2C%20Reetika%20Khera%2C%20and%20Anmol%20Somanchi%2C%202021).%20Such%20a%20digitalwashing%20of%20rights%20raise%20serious%20apprehensions%20of%20whether%20we%20are%20entering%20a%20new%20age%20of%20digital%20feudalism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20all%20recipes%20for%20diluting%20government%20accountability%20and%20transfer%20duties%20%E2%80%93%20and%20blame%20%E2%80%93%20from%20the%20government%20to%20the%20individual.%C2%A0Such%20a%20model%20of%20policy%20and%20governance%20atomises%20the%20poor%2C%20who%20are%20left%20with%20little%20promise%20in%20making%20their%20rights%20count.%20They%20are%20pushed%20to%20the%20periphery%20to%20live%20a%20shadowed%20existence.%20Being%20in%20constant%20precarity%20means%20that%20the%20poor%20have%20little%20or%20no%20claim%20making%20in%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECounter-majoritarian%20constitutionalism%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20essential%20services%20like%20transportation%2C%20healthcare%20and%20education%20are%20undergoing%20unprecedented%20levels%20of%20compartmentalising%20along%20class%20%E2%80%93%20and%20caste%20%E2%80%93%20lines.%20In%20such%20segregated%20sensual%20experiences%20of%20India%2C%20spaces%20for%20cross-class%2C%20cross-caste%20intermingling%20are%20shrinking.%20These%20in%20turn%20have%20further%20ossified%20the%20affluent%20and%20widened%20the%20blind%20spots%20towards%20deprivation.%20As%20Jean%20Dr%C3%A8ze%20and%20Amartya%20Sen%20write%C2%A0in%20their%20remarkable%20book%2C%20%3Cem%3EIndia%3A%20An%20Uncertain%20Glory%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20India%20is%20like%20%E2%80%98pockets%20of%20California%20in%20sub-Saharan%20Africa.%E2%80%99%20Beyond%20the%20aphoristic%20quality%20of%20this%20phrase%20is%20the%20quotidian%20acceptance%20of%20this%20fact.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERising%20economic%20inequality%20and%20segregation%20will%20naturally%20result%20in%20a%20%E2%80%98social%20production%20of%20indifference%E2%80%99%20towards%20the%20poor%20(Gupta%2C%202012).%20When%20there%20is%20no%20meaningful%20interaction%20across%20class%2C%20caste%20and%20religion%2C%20the%20deprived%20sections%20become%20part%20of%20a%20physically%20proximate%20but%20emotionally%20distant%20landscape.%20A%20natural%20fallout%20of%20such%20a%20gradual%20process%20of%20emotional%20dissonance%20is%20a%20structural%20erosion%20of%20compassion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECounterpoint%20to%20the%20structurally%20spawned%20apathy%20towards%20the%20poor%20is%20the%20regular%20mantras%20of%20prejudice%20towards%20religious%20minorities.%20(To%20be%20sure%2C%20historically%20marginalised%20communities%20such%20as%20Dalits%20and%20Adivasis%20are%20also%20targets%20of%20prejudice%20but%20in%20this%20article%20we%20focus%20on%20the%20communal%20dimension.)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20eminent%20scholar%20of%20jurisprudence%20Ronald%20Dworkin%20underscored%20the%20need%20to%20practise%20constitutionalism%20as%20a%20counter-majoritarian%20force%20for%20a%20healthy%20society.%20Reflecting%20on%20the%20American%20constitution%20in%20this%20regard%2C%20he%20wrote%20in%20%3Cem%3ETaking%20Rights%20Seriously%3C%2Fem%3E%20(133)%3A%20%E2%80%9DThe%20constitution%2C%20and%20particularly%20the%20Bill%20of%20Rights%2C%20is%20designed%20to%20protect%20individual%20citizens%20and%20groups%20against%20certain%20decisions%20that%20a%20majority%20of%20citizens%20might%20want%20to%20make%2C%20even%20when%20the%20majority%20acts%20in%20what%20it%20takes%20to%20be%20the%20general%20or%20common%20interest.%20Such%20protection%20is%20rooted%20in%20the%20moral%20rights%20which%20individuals%20possess%20against%20the%20majority.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESocio-economic%20policies%20as%20per%20the%20Directive%20Principles%20of%20State%20Policy%20of%20the%20Indian%20constitution%20should%20foster%20a%20more%20level%20playing%20field%20across%20caste%20and%20class%20lines.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20despite%20our%20progressive%20constitution%20with%20built-in%20counter-majoritarian%20principles%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0both%20in%20fundamental%20rights%20and%20in%20institutional%20responsibilities%20%E2%80%93%20there%20are%20serious%20concerns.%20In%20contrast%20to%20constitutional%20values%2C%20the%20majoritarian%20nationalism%20espoused%20by%20Hindutva%20ideologues%20rests%20on%20retaining%20the%20cruel%20caste%20hierarchy%20and%20treating%20Muslims%20as%20evil.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fmajoritarianism-religious-discrimination-mediocrity-panic%5C%22%3EThe%20Many%20Dimensions%20of%20Majoritarianism%20Beyond%20Religious%20Discrimination%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDiscriminatory%20legalism%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMajoritarianism%20represents%20a%20specific%20form%20of%20control%20and%20tyranny%20whose%20assertion%20in%20an%20electoral%20democracy%20is%20possible%20only%20when%20the%20elected%20government%20in%20power%20sets%20the%20tone%20and%20template%20for%20the%20everyday%20enactment%20of%20such%20tyranny.%C2%A0The%20success%20of%20such%20a%20project%20rests%20on%20a%20continuous%20injection%20of%20resentment%20maligning%20specific%20minority%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20book%20%3Cem%3EHow%20Fascism%20Works%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Jason%20Stanely%20writes%2C%20%E2%80%9CAt%20the%20core%20of%20fascism%20is%20loyalty%20to%20tribe%2C%20ethnic%20identity%2C%20religion%2C%20tradition%2C%20or%20in%20a%20word%2C%20%3Cem%3Enation%3C%2Fem%3E.%20But%2C%20in%20stark%20contrast%20to%20a%20version%20of%20nationalism%20with%20equality%20as%20its%20goal%2C%20fascist%20nationalism%20is%20a%20repudiation%20of%20the%20liberal%20democratic%20ideal%3B%20it%20is%20nationalism%20in%20the%20service%20of%20domination%2C%20with%20the%20goal%20of%20preserving%2C%20maintaining%2C%20or%20gaining%20a%20position%20at%20the%20top%20of%20a%20hierarchy%20of%20power%20and%20status%E2%80%9D(97).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20Hindutva%20variant%20of%20fascism%2C%20even%20a%20catastrophe%20like%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20was%20not%20spared.%20Puzzled%20by%20the%20evident%20lack%20of%20anger%20towards%20the%20regime%20during%20the%20lockdowns%2C%20Mohammad%20Sajjad%20provocatively%20posits%20if%20communal%20hatred%20has%20superseded%20food%20and%20livelihood%20insecurity%20amongst%20us.%20Emboldened%20by%20prejudicial%20speech%20from%20the%20top%2C%20the%20author%20notes%20that%20some%20television%20anchors%20during%20lockdowns%20referred%20to%20stranded%20Muslim%20pilgrims%20as%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Echhupey%20huey%3C%2Fem%3E%20(hiding)%E2%80%99%20while%20Hindus%20stuck%20in%20places%20like%20in%20the%20Vaishno%20Devi%20temple%20were%20termed%20as%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Ephansey%20huey%3C%2Fem%3E%20(stranded)%E2%80%99%20(Sajjad%202022).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20recently%2C%20a%20fact-finding%20report%20by%20the%20Centre%20for%20Study%20of%20Society%20and%20Secularism%20on%20the%20violence%20that%20erupted%20in%20Nuh%2C%20Haryana%2C%20in%20August%202023%20presents%20a%20chilling%20account%20of%20the%20ecosystem%20of%20hatred%20that%20has%20been%20created%20by%20Hindutva%20forces.%20In%20response%20to%20the%20violence%2C%20using%20bulldozers%2C%20the%20Haryana%20administration%20under%20the%20political%20patronage%20of%20the%20BJP%2C%20demolished%20750%20properties%20in%20Nuh%20alone%2C%20all%20belonging%20to%20Muslims.%20A%20Muslim%20shopkeeper%20whose%20shops%20were%20demolished%20said%2C%20%E2%80%98Our%20shops%20were%20targeted%20because%20we%20are%20Muslims.%20There%20is%20nothing%20more%20to%20the%20demolitions.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20an%20abuse%20of%20power%20in%20the%20name%20of%20law%20and%20order%20is%20what%20the%20political%20philosopher%20Jan%20Werner%20Muller%20refers%20to%20as%20%E2%80%98discriminatory%20legalism%E2%80%99%20which%20translates%20to%20%E2%80%98for%20my%20friends%20everything%2C%20for%20others%2C%20the%20law.%E2%80%99%C2%A0Such%20a%20targeted%20bulldozing%20of%20Muslim%20homes%20sends%20a%20strong%20message%20that%20the%20citizenship%20of%20Muslims%20weighs%20less%20than%20the%20citizenship%20of%20their%20caste%20Hindu%20neighbours.%20It%20is%20hardly%20surprising%20then%20that%20a%20remorseless%20Hindu%20policeman%2C%20Chetan%20Singh%2C%20will%20shoot%20and%20kill%203%20Muslim%20men%20from%20a%20point-blank%20range%20on%20a%20train%20just%20because%20they%20are%20Muslims.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20active%20perpetrators%20of%20violence%20are%20perhaps%20operating%20on%20the%20principle%20of%20Schadenfreude%20(deriving%20pleasure%20from%20others%E2%80%99%20misery)%2C%20it%20is%20hard%20to%20fathom%20the%20mindset%20of%20those%20on%20the%20fence%2C%20the%20bystanders.%20Surely%2C%20not%20everyone%20enjoys%20seeing%20destructive%20acts%20causing%C2%A0misery.%20Writing%20about%20the%20bystanders%20in%20Israel%20in%20the%201990s%20despite%20widespread%20awareness%20of%20the%20nature%20of%20crimes%20committed%20by%20Israel%20on%20Palestinian%20people%2C%20the%20criminologist%20and%20human%20rights%20activist%20Stanley%20Cohen%20referred%20to%20it%20as%20the%20sociology%20and%20culture%20of%20denial.%20He%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1177%2F000486589302600201%3FjournalCode%3Danja%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%98Why%2C%20when%20faced%20by%20knowledge%20of%20others%E2%80%99%20suffering%20and%20pain%20%E2%80%93%20particularly%20the%20suffering%20and%20pain%20resulting%20from%20what%20are%20called%20%E2%80%9Chuman%20rights%20violations%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20does%20%E2%80%9Creaction%E2%80%9D%20so%20often%20take%20the%20form%20of%20denial%2C%20avoidance%2C%20passivity%2C%20indifference%2C%20rationalisation%20or%20collusion%3F%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20a%20culture%20of%20denial%20continues%20in%20India%20and%20is%20a%20pathway%20to%20putrid%20perversion.%20Despite%20the%20Sangh%20Parivar%E2%80%99s%20clear%20avowal%20of%20treating%20Muslims%20with%20derision%2C%20from%20the%20standpoint%20of%20humanity%2C%20when%20so%20many%20Hindus%20remain%20bystanders%20to%20communalism%20and%20discrimination%2C%20it%20points%20to%20how%20compassion%20in%20us%20has%20been%20corroded.%20When%20tragedy%20and%20humanitarian%20crises%20experienced%20by%20one%20community%2C%20as%20in%20the%20genocide%20in%20Palestine%2C%20get%20celebrated%20by%20Hindutva%20groups%2C%20it%20is%20not%20just%20Islamophobia.%20It%20symbolises%20perverted%20pleasure.%20Islamophobia%20seems%20too%20mild%20and%20an%20inaccurate%20term.%20Islamoperversion%20or%20treating%20Muslims%20with%20derision%20might%20be%20more%20appropriate%20to%20describe%20the%20extent%20of%20corrosion%20of%20compassion%20for%20political%20gains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20backdrop%20of%20such%20continued%20denigration%20of%20Muslims%2C%20the%20government%20led%20frenzy%20and%20the%20loud%20celebration%20of%20many%20on%20the%20consecration%20of%20the%20Ram%20temple%20in%20Ayodhya%20speaks%20neither%20about%20nonviolent%20devotion%20nor%20about%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20adherence%20to%20constitutional%20values.%20But%20instead%2C%20it%20shows%20how%20the%20corrosion%20of%20compassion%20has%20led%20to%20the%20removal%20of%20the%20veil%20of%20decency%20and%20respect.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOur%20moral%20core%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20summary%2C%20an%20X-Ray%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20compassion%20looks%20damaged.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20we%20embark%20on%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20in%202024%2C%20we%20need%20to%20think%20hard%20about%20our%20priorities%20and%20imaginations%20of%20India.%20If%20we%20continue%20with%20the%20politics%20of%20precarity%20and%20prejudice%2C%20we%20will%20be%20vaccinating%20our%20society%20against%20compassion.%20This%20will%20result%20in%20a%20generation%20where%20mistrust%2C%20anxiety%20and%20prejudice%20would%20be%20the%20currency%20of%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20choice%20is%20ours.%20Do%20we%20want%20an%20India%20with%20humanity%20and%20empathy%2C%20or%20do%20we%20want%20an%20India%20where%20our%20moral%20core%20is%20hollowed%20out%20leaving%20behind%20a%20residue%20of%20soulless%20automatons%3F%20In%20this%20context%2C%20the%20celebrated%20saviours%2C%20the%20rat-hole%20miners%2C%20have%20some%20important%20advice%20for%20us.%20After%20rescuing%20the%20trapped%20workers%2C%20the%20rat-hole%20miners%20%E2%80%93%20most%20of%20whom%20are%20Muslims%20and%20Dalits%20%E2%80%93%20were%20asked%20what%20they%20want%2C%20their%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fnever-got-so-much-praise-for-doing-our-jobs-say-muslim-and-dalit-rat-hole-miners-who-rescued-trapped-silkyara-workers%2Farticle67587279.ece%5C%22%3Eresponse%3C%2Fa%3E%20captures%20what%20the%20country%20really%20needs%3A%C2%A0%E2%80%98a%20pucca%20house%20for%20an%20elderly%20mother%2C%20village%20roads%2C%20love%20and%20human%20dignity%20that%20crosses%20religious%20and%20caste%20lines%2C%20life%20insurance%20and%20fair%20wages%20for%20all%20workers%2C%20and%20an%20assurance%20that%20such%20a%20collapse%20is%20not%20allowed%20to%20happen%20again.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20views%20expressed%20are%20personal%20and%20do%20not%20reflect%20the%20views%20of%20the%20institutions%20I%20am%20part%20of.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAcknowledgements%3A%20Many%20thanks%20to%20Sayandeb%20Chowdhury%20for%20feedback%20on%20earlier%20drafts%20of%20this%20article.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERajendran%20Narayanan%20teaches%20in%20Azim%20Premji%20University%2C%20Bangalore%20and%20is%20affiliated%20with%20LibTech%20India.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theindiaforum.in%2Fpublic-policy%2Fx-ray-indias-compassion%5C%22%3Epublished%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20India%20Forum.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710333021000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F13162917%2Fsonika-agarwal-XCJkr6Is0B8-unsplash1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwhat-would-an-x-ray-of-indias-compassion-reveal%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20politics%20of%20precarity%20and%20heightened%20socio-economic%20inequality%20erodes%20our%20compassion.%20The%20politics%20of%20prejudice%20and%20the%20treatment%20of%20minorities%20corrodes%20it.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwhat-would-an-x-ra