hief-justices-praise-as-top-court-cooks-daughter-bags-us-scholarships-5231557%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BCAA%20Is%20A%20Parliamentary%20Recognition%20Of%20Neighbourhood%20Situation%26quot%3B%3A%20Sources%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%20%26quot%3Bdoes%20not%20discriminate%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20religion%2C%26quot%3B%20government%20sources%20told%20NDTV%20today%2C%20clarifying%20on%20a%20criticism%20that%20Opposition%20has%20been%20levelling%20since%20the%20draft%20bill%20was%20drawn%20up.%20The%20classification%20on%20basis%20of%20religion%20is%20due%20to%20the%20%26quot%3Bneighbourhood%20situation%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20has%20said%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%20will%20help%20minorities%20from%20three%20neighbouring%20countries%20--%20Pakistan%2C%20Afghanistan%20and%20Bangladesh%20--%20get%20citizenship%20if%20they%20fled%20due%20to%20religious%20persecution%20and%20settled%20in%20India%20before%20December%2031%2C%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECritics%2C%20however%2C%20claim%20it%20discriminates%20against%20Muslims%20and%20violates%20the%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESources%20today%20said%20the%20CAA%20%26quot%3Bprotects%20minorities%20in%20countries%20which%20have%20a%20state%20religion%26quot%3B.%20%26quot%3BThe%20presence%20of%20a%20state%20religion%20is%20hurting%20minorities%20in%20the%20neighbourhood%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20three%20nations%20in%20question%20are%20Muslim%20dominated.%20The%20CAA%2C%20passed%20in%202019%2C%20covers%20Hindus%2C%20Sikhs%2C%20Christians%2C%20Parsis%2C%20Buddhists%20and%20Jains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20law%20also%20does%20not%20impact%20citizenship%20rules%20of%20India%2C%20sources%20said.%20It%20only%20fast-tracks%20citizenship%20for%20those%20persecuted%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20has%20said%20the%20CAA%20only%20reduces%20the%20waiting%20period%20for%20filing%20an%20application%20for%20citizenship%20to%20qualifying%20individuals%20from%2011%20years%20to%20five.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20does%20not%20discriminate%20against%20Muslims%20from%20those%20nations%20who%20wish%20to%20apply%20for%20Indian%20citizenship.%20%26quot%3BCAA%20does%20not%20cancel%20naturalisation%20laws.%20Therefore%2C%20any%20person%2C%20including%20Muslim%20migrants%20from%20foreign%20countries%2C%20seeking%20to%20be%20an%20Indian%20citizen%2C%20can%20apply%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20government%20has%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESources%20also%20said%20Pakistan%20did%20not%20honour%20the%20%26quot%3BNehru-Liaquat%20pact%26quot%3B%E2%80%94a%20treaty%20drawn%20up%20in%201950%20and%20signed%20by%20India's%20first%20Prime%20Minister%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20and%20his%20Pakistan%20counterpart%20Liaquat%20Ali%20Khan.%20%26quot%3BIndia%20raised%20this%20matter%20at%20the%20United%20Nations%C2%A0%20unsuccessfully%2C%26quot%3B%20sources%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Nehru-Liaquat%20pact%20assured%20minorities%20the%20same%20rights%20as%20the%20majority%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Pakistan%20and%20the%20Indian%20government%2C%20it%20said%2C%20will%20ensure%20%26quot%3Bcomplete%20equality%20of%20citizenship%2C%20irrespective%20of%20religion%2C%20a%20full%20sense%20of%20security%20in%20respect%20of%20life%2C%20culture%2C%20property%20and%20personal%20honour%2C%20freedom%20of%20movement%20within%20each%20country%20and%20freedom%20of%20occupation%2C%20speech%20and%20worship%2C%20subject%20to%20law%20and%20morality%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20would%20participate%20in%20public%20life%2C%20hold%20political%20or%20other%20office%2C%20and%20serve%20in%20their%20country's%20civil%20and%20armed%20forces.%20%26quot%3BBoth%20governments%20declare%20these%20rights%20to%20be%20fundamental%20and%20undertake%20to%20enforce%20them%20effectively%2C%26quot%3B%20read%20the%20treaty.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710332400000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22htt