ngQYE7EwHGg%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2F6e7bffd8-5768-4cc3-acba-19d57f03b92c%3Fj%253DeyJ1IjoiaHpuMnUifQ.MQOquijPBw98XVYBc9m195DW7Qx9ruSvngQYE7EwHGg%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1710402127301000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw2LlVElOTqcp0HhVOD3GMt9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etargeted%20with%20Pegasus%20spyware%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20extraordinary%20that%20two%20ECs%20have%20resigned%20during%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20tenure%2C%20indicating%20in%20no%20uncertain%20terms%20that%20all%20is%20not%20well%20with%20a%20body%20which%20is%20mandated%20to%20conduct%20free%20and%20fair%20elections%20%E2%80%93%20which%20in%20turn%20have%20been%20held%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20be%20part%20of%20the%20constitution%E2%80%99s%20basic%20structure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Election%20Commission%20commanded%20high%20respect%20and%20admiration%20from%20within%20India%20and%20abroad%20and%20during%20its%20golden%20jubilee%20celebrations%20in%202000%2C%20former%20President%20K.R.%20Narayanan%20quoted%20a%20public%20opinion%20poll%20according%20to%20which%20people%20rated%20the%20Election%20Commission%20very%20highly%20%E2%80%93%20far%20ahead%20of%20the%20police%2C%20the%20bureaucracy%2C%20political%20parties%2C%20the%20Union%20government%2C%20local%20self%20government%20and%20even%20the%20judiciary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EApprehensions%20expressed%20in%20Constituent%20Assembly%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArun%20Goel%E2%80%99s%20resignation%20and%20Lavasa%E2%80%99s%20earlier%20resignation%20are%20part%20of%20the%20unmistakable%20trend%20of%20the%20decline%20and%20fall%20of%20the%20high%20benchmarks%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20impartiality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESadly%2C%20with%20retrospect%2C%20the%20alarming%20collapse%20of%20the%20commission%E2%80%99s%20independence%20reflects%20apprehensions%20of%20two%20distinguished%20members%20of%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%2C%20Shibban%20Lal%20Saxena%20and%20Hriday%20Nath%20Kunzru%2C%20as%20well%20as%20of%20B.R.%20Ambedkar%2C%20chairman%20of%20the%20drafting%20committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20June%2015%2C%201949%2C%20during%20the%20discussion%20on%20Article%20289%20in%20the%20draft%20constitution%2C%20which%20concerned%20the%20Election%20Commission%2C%20Saxena%20presciently%20but%20poignantly%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20quite%20possible%20that%20some%20party%20in%20power%20who%20wants%20to%20win%20the%20next%20election%20may%20appoint%20a%20staunch%20party%20man%20as%20chief%20commissioner.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20then%20with%20sadness%20could%20foresee%20a%20period%20in%20the%20evolution%20of%20our%20country%20when%20there%20might%20not%20be%20another%20prime%20minister%20like%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%2C%20who%20was%20known%20for%20his%20independence%20and%20impartiality%2C%20and%20when%20someone%20getting%20elected%20to%20that%20office%20might%20abuse%20their%20power%20and%20authority%20by%20appointing%20an%20unworthy%20EC%2C%20subverting%20the%20electoral%20process%20and%20the%20very%20foundation%20of%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20day%20later%2C%20on%20June%2016%2C%20Kunzru%20in%20his%20speech%20warned%20that%20if%20the%20electoral%20machinery%20would%20become%20defective%2C%20inefficient%20or%20be%20run%20by%20people%20of%20doubtful%20integrity%2C%20%E2%80%9Cdemocracy%20will%20be%20poisoned%20at%20the%20source%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20cautioned%20that%20instead%20of%20learning%20how%20the%20judicious%20use%20of%20their%20vote%20can%20reform%20the%20administration%2C%20people%20should%20not%20end%20up%20learning%20how%20to%20get%20what%20they%20want%20through%20intrigue%20and%20unfair%20means.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAmbedkar%E2%80%99s%20apprehensions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmbedkar%20feared%20that%20the%20Election%20Commission%20might%20%E2%80%9Ccome%20under%20the%20thumb%20of%20the%20executive%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20any%20provision%20in%20the%20constitution%20preventing%20the%20government%20of%20the%20day%20from%20appointing%20unworthy%20people%20to%20the%20poll%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20its%20order%20of%20March%202023%20reiterated%20those%20apprehensions%20when%20it%20said%20that%20to%20prevent%20the%20Election%20Commission%20from%20becoming%20%E2%80%9Ca%20servile%20commission%E2%80%9D%2C%20a%20committee%20consisting%20of%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20and%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20opposition%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20or%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20opposition%20party%20with%20the%20largest%20number%20of%20MPs%20should%20recommend%20candidates%20for%20appointment%20to%20the%20poll%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETragically%2C%20the%20Modi%20regime%E2%80%99s%20law%20replaced%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20with%20a%20Union%20minister%20to%20be%20chosen%20by%20the%20prime%20minister.%20The%20resignations%20of%20two%20ECs%20and%20the%20alteration%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20order%20during%20the%20Modi%20regime%20form%20part%20of%20the%20alarming%20pattern%20of%20the%20decline%20of%20our%20democracy%E2%80%99s%20institutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ES.N.%20Sahu%20served%20as%20an%20officer%20on%20special%20duty%20to%20former%20President%20K.R.%20Narayanan.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710318647000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F13134450%2Fimage-1945.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fresignations-of-two-election-commissioners-under-modi-regime-reflect-ecis-decline%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Just%20a%20few%20days%20before%20the%20announcement%20of%20the%20general%20elections%2C%20election%20commissioner%20Arun%20Goel%20resigned.%20Ashok%20Lavasa%2C%20who%20was%20appointed%20an%20EC%20in%202018%2C%20gave%20several%20dissenting%20notes%20on%20the%20issue%20of%20PM%20Modi%20and%20Amit%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20alleged%20infringement%20of%20the%20campaigning%20rules%20in%20the%202019%20election.%20He%20resigned%20in%20August%202020.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fresignations-of-two-election-commissioners-under-modi-regime-reflect-ecis-decline%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Government's%20Explainer%20On%20Citizenship%20Law%20Amid%20Opposition%20Attacks%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20amendments%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ftopic%2Fcitizenship-amendment-act%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecitizenship%20law%3C%2Fa%3E%20-%20passed%20by%20Parliament%20in%202019%20and%20notified%20by%20the%20government%20Monday%20evening%2C%20to%20come%20into%20effect%20weeks%20before%20the%20general%20election%20-%20have%20triggered%20a%20back-and-forth%20with%20the%20opposition%20accusing%20the%20ruling%20BJP%20of%20polarising%20voters%2C%20and%20the%20government%2C%20hitting%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmidst%20this%20opposition%20pushback%2C%20the%20Union%20Home%20Ministry%20has%20released%20a%20statement%20clarifying%20various%20points%20within%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ftopic%2Fcaa%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECAA%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20answering%20questions%20raised%20by%20its%20critics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Has%20Government%20Said%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20point%20in%20the%20government's%20rebuttal%20is%20to%20stress%20that%20Indian%20Muslims'%20citizenship%20rights%20will%20not%20be%20rescinded%20or%20scrapped.%20The%20estimated%2018%20crore%20Muslim%20population%20in%20India%20has%20%26quot%3Bequal%20rights%20as%20any%20other%20Indian%20citizen%26quot%3B%2C%20the%20government%20clarified%20in%20its%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%2C%20the%20government%20has%20said%2C%20concerns%20only%20Hindus%2C%20Sikhs%2C%20Christians%2C%20Parsis%2C%20Buddhists%2C%20or%20Jains%20from%20three%20Muslim-majority%20nations%20-%20Bangladesh%2C%20Afghanistan%2C%20and%20Pakistan%20-%20who%20fled%20due%20to%20religious%20persecution%20and%20entered%20India%20on%20or%20before%20December%2031%2C%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EREAD%20%7C%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcitizenship-amendment-act-does-caa-put-any-restrictions-on-muslim-migrants-what-government-said-5226063%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDoes%20CAA%20Restrict%20Muslim%20Migrants%3F%20What%20Government%20Said%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20CAA%20only%20reduces%20the%20waiting%20period%20for%20application%20of%20citizenship%20-%20to%20qualifying%20individuals%20-%20from%2011%20years%20to%20five.%20In%20an%20earlier%20clarification%2C%20the%20Home%20Ministry%20also%20insisted%20the%20CAA%20%26quot%3Bdoes%20not%20prevent%20any%20Muslim%2C%20who%20is%20persecuted%20in%20those%20countries%20for%20practising%20their%20version%20of%20Islam%2C%20from%20applying%20for%20Indian%20citizenship%20under%20the%20existing%20laws%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECrucially%2C%20the%20CAA%20also%20has%20no%20provision%20for%20deportation%20of%20individuals%20from%20the%20above%20three%20countries%20who%20have%20been%20found%20living%20illegally%20in%20India%2C%20the%20government%20said.%20This%20is%20because%20%26quot%3BIndia%20has%20no%20agreement%20with%20any%20of%20these%20three%20to%20repatriate%20migrants%26quot%3B%2C%20the%20government%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20there%20is%20no%20question%20about%20repatriation%2C%20it%20clarified.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EREAD%20%7C%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2F4-years-after-bill-passed-citizenship-law-caa-becomes-reality-5218643%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E4%20Years%20After%20Bill%20Passed%2C%20Citizenship%20Law%20CAA%20Becomes%20Reality%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20from%20that%20point%2C%20the%20government%20also%20dismissed%20rumours%20Indian%20citizens%20-%20the%20reference%20being%20to%20Muslims%20-%20will%20be%20asked%20to%20maintain%2C%20and%20show%2C%20citizenship%20papers.%20%26quot%3BNo%20Indian%20citizen%20will%20be%20asked%20to%20produce%20any%20document%20to%20prove%20citizenship%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20ministry%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20the%20government%20also%20shut%20down%20talk%20Muslims%20from%20other%20countries%20can%20not%20apply%20for%20citizenship.%20%26quot%3BCAA%20does%20not%20cancel%20naturalisation%20laws.%20Therefore%2C%20any%20person%2C%20including%20Muslim%20migrants%20from%20foreign%20countries%2C%20seeking%20to%20be%20an%20Indian%20citizen%2C%20can%20apply...%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20found%20eligible%20under%20the%20current%20laws%2C%20all%20such%20individuals%20will%20be%20given%20citizenship%2C%20the%20Home%20Ministry%20has%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Has%20Opposition%20Said%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECongress%20boss%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%20has%20slammed%20the%20notification%20of%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%2C%20or%20CAA%2C%20as%20the%20BJP's%20%26quot%3Bdesperate%20attempt%20at%20divisive%20politics%26quot%3B.%20Mr%20Kharge's%20party%20has%20also%20accused%20the%20BJP%20of%20trying%20to%20divide%20voters%2C%20particularly%20in%20Bengal%20and%20Assam.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20has%20also%20pointed%20to%20the%20four-year%20delay%20in%20notifying%20the%20CAA%2C%20which%20was%20one%20of%20the%20BJP's%20biggest%20campaign%20promises%20ahead%20of%20the%202019%20election%2C%20observing%20it%20was%20finally%20done%20just%20before%20the%202024%20poll%2C%20when%20the%20saffron%20party%20can%20list%20it%20as%20a%20major%20achievement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EREAD%20%7C%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdesigned-to-polarise-elect