42088%230%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Philippine%20President%20Marcos%20says%20Manila%20did%20not%20reject%20the%20deal%2C%20which%20he%20called%20%26quot%3Bquestionable%26quot%3B.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A157%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-68542088%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-68542088.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-68542088.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22IO%20Whose%20Role%20Bombay%20HC%20Questioned%20in%20Saibaba%20Case%20Was%20Also%20Part%20of%20Elgar%20Parishad%20Probe%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F13111914%2FBKzOcnek_400x400.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMumbai%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%202018%2C%20when%20the%20Pune%20police%20first%20filed%20a%20chargesheet%20in%20the%20Elgar%20Parishad%20case%2C%20they%20claimed%20to%20be%20%E2%80%9Cheavily%20relying%E2%80%9D%20on%20the%20investigation%20conducted%20in%20the%20case%20involving%20former%20Delhi%20University%20professor%20G.N.%20Saibaba.%20By%20then%2C%20Saibaba%20and%20five%20others%20had%20already%20been%20convicted%20by%20the%20Gadchiroli%20sessions%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Pune%20police%2C%20at%20multiple%20places%20in%20the%20Elgar%20Parishad%20chargesheet%2C%20claimed%20that%20some%20of%20those%20arrested%20in%20the%20Elgar%20Parishad%20case%20had%20a%20%E2%80%9Cdirect%20association%E2%80%9D%20with%20Saibaba.%20They%20focused%20on%20the%20Gadchiroli%20court%E2%80%99s%20life%20punishment%20granted%20to%20Saibaba%20to%20build%20their%20case%20against%20the%20human%20rights%20defenders%20arrested%20in%20the%20Elgar%20Parishad%20case.%20The%20Pune%20police%E2%80%99s%20chargesheet%20was%20later%20adopted%20as-is%20by%20the%20National%20Investigation%20Agency%20(NIA)%2C%20which%20took%20over%20the%20case%20in%20early%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%20that%20the%20Nagpur%20bench%20of%20the%20Bombay%20high%20court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fbombay-hc-acquits-g-n-saibaba-and-five-others-in-uapa-case%5C%22%3Ehas%20acquitted%20Saibaba%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20five%20others%20of%20all%20charges%20(not%20once%20but%20twice)%20and%20the%20Maharashtra%20state%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fvery-well-reasoned-sc-refuses-to-stay-bombay-hc-order-acquitting-saibaba-others%5C%22%3Efailed%20to%20secure%20a%20stay%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20acquittal%20both%20in%20the%20high%20court%20and%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20the%20role%20of%20the%20state%20police%20needs%20to%20be%20closely%20examined.%20More%20so%2C%20because%20besides%20the%20police%E2%80%99s%20attempt%20to%20drag%20Saibaba%20into%20the%20Elgar%20Parishad%20case%2C%20the%20investigating%20officer%20Suhas%20Bawche%20in%20the%20Saibaba%20case%20also%20plays%20a%20substantial%20role%20in%20the%20investigation%20of%20the%20Elgar%20Parishad%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20293-page%20judgement%20delivered%20by%20the%20division%20bench%20of%20Justices%20Vinay%20G.%20Joshi%20and%20Valimiki%20S.%20Menezes%20of%20the%20Nagpur%20bench%20of%20the%20Bombay%20high%20court%2C%20along%20with%20the%20technical%20lapses%2C%20the%20judges%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsaibaba-acquittal-from-lack-of-sanction-to-dodgy-evidence-high-court-judgment-tears-into-states-case%5C%22%3Especifically%20raised%20suspicion%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20the%20investigation%20conducted%20by%20investigating%20officer%20Bawche.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBawche%2C%20who%20was%20Sub-divisional%20Police%20Officer%20(SDPO)%20at%20Aheri%20in%20Gadchiroli%20district%20at%20that%20time%2C%20had%20led%20the%20investigation%20in%20Saibaba%E2%80%99s%20case.%20His%20claim%20was%20that%20Saibaba%20and%20five%20others%20%E2%80%93%20Prashant%20Rahi%2C%20Mahesh%20Tikri%2C%20Hem%20Keshwdatta%20Mishra%2C%20Pandu%20Narote%20and%20Vijay%20Nan%20Tikri%20%E2%80%93%20were%20a%20part%20of%20the%20Revolutionary%20Democratic%20Front%2C%20a%20frontal%20organisation%20of%20the%20banned%20CPI%20(Maoist)%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20claims%2C%20now%20proved%20baseless%2C%20were%20based%20on%20the%20police%20and%20panch%20witnesses%E2%80%99%20statements%20that%20the%20high%20court%20has%20now%20raised%20serious%20questions%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20defence%20lawyers%20had%20contested%20that%20Mishra%2C%20one%20of%20the%20six%20persons%20who%20faced%20a%20decade-long%20incarceration%20in%20the%20case%2C%20was%20arrested%20two%20days%20before%20he%20was%20actually%20shown%20arrested%20on%20August%2022%2C%202013.%20The%20police%20claimed%20that%20Mishra%2C%20along%20with%20Tikri%20and%20Narote%2C%20was%20apprehended%20from%20a%20%E2%80%9Csecluded%20place%E2%80%9D%20near%20Aheri%20bus%20stop%20around%206%20pm.%20The%20prosecution%20witnesses%2C%20all%20comprising%20policemen%20and%20panchas%2C%20had%20claimed%20that%20from%20the%20time%20of%20spotting%20them%20at%20the%20bus%20stop%20to%20seizing%20%E2%80%9Cevidences%E2%80%9D%20and%20summoning%20witnesses%20before%20whom%20the%20seizures%20were%20conducted%2C%20the%20process%20took%20less%20than%20an%20hour%20and%20half.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20panch%20witness%2C%20one%20Santosh%20Bawne%2C%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Cstock%20witness%E2%80%9D%20who%20regularly%20appeared%20as%20a%20witness%20for%20the%20police.%20Bawne%2C%20who%20had%20no%20formal%20education%20and%20no%20knowledge%20of%20electronic%20devices%2C%20was%20made%20to%20stand%20as%20witness%20to%20the%20seizures%20of%20electronic%20evidence.%20Bawne%20claimed%20to%20reached%20the%20police%20station%20within%205-10%20minutes%20after%20being%20summoned.%20This%2C%20the%20court%20has%20raised%20doubts%20about%2C%20considering%20he%20was%20at%20a%20different%20location.%20Interestingly%2C%20Bawne%20had%20claimed%20that%20he%20was%20summoned%20to%20the%20police%20station%20by%20one%20Narendra%20Dube%2C%20a%20station%20diary%20duty%20incharge%20constable.%20But%20Dube%20had%20denied%20having%20summoned%20Bawne%20to%20the%20police%20station.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judges%20have%20also%20pointed%20to%20the%20chain%20of%20events%20that%20start%20around%206%3A15%20pm%20at%20the%20bus%20stop.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20seen%20the%20chain%20of%20events%20that%20at%2006.15%20p.m.%2C%20the%20accused%20were%20for%20first%20time%20accosted%20near%20Aheri%20Bus-stand.%20It%20would%20certainly%20take%20a%20few%20minutes%20to%20interact%20and%20then%2C%20further%2C%20some%20more%20time%20would%20be%20required%20to%20bring%20them%20to%20the%20Police%20Station%E2%80%A6%20In%20substance%2C%20from%20the%20first%20interaction%20with%20accused%20at%2006.15%20p.m.%2C%20all%20preliminary%20steps%20were%20taken%20within%20just%2015%20minutes%20and%20then%20seizure%20panchnama%20has%20commenced%2C%20which%20is%20improbable%20and%20requires%20to%20be%20noted%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20judgment%20reads.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20defence%20lawyers%20had%20accused%20the%20police%20of%20presenting%20an%20antedated%20FIR%20and%20adding%20dates%20and%20other%20details%20later%20to%20suit%20their%20narrative.%20The%20court%20took%20note%20of%20the%20different%20colour%20inks%20used%20in%20the%20FIR.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20may%20hasten%20to%20add%20that%20copy%20of%20FIR%20(Exh.%20221)%20is%20a%20carbon%20copy%20on%20which%20the%20time%20is%20mentioned%20in%20blue%20ink%2C%20whilst%20the%20time%20and%20general%20diary%20reference%20is%20in%20black%20ink.%20We%20do%20not%20find%20any%20explanation%20coming%20forth%20in%20this%20regard%20from%20the%20prosecution%20to%20remove%20this%20doubt%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20judges%20write.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20defence%20lawyers%20had%20accused%20Bawche%20and%20his%20team%20of%20%E2%80%9Cmanipulating%20the%20police%20record%20and%20fabricating%20incriminating%20material%E2%80%9D.%20The%20court%20took%20note%20of%20the%20condition%20of%20the%20case%20diary%20and%20how%20the%20police%20had%20resorted%20to%20recording%20entries%20on%20loose%20papers.%20Case%20diaries%20are%20an%20important%20piece%20of%20evidence%20in%20criminal%20trials.%20Police%20have%20to%20record%20every%20move%20in%20the%20case%20diary%20and%20these%20entries%20made%20in%20the%20case%20diary%20prove%20to%20be%20a%20crucial%20piece%20of%20evidence%20at%20the%20time%20of%20trials.%20In%20this%20case%2C%20however%2C%20the%20police%20had%20failed%20to%20follow%20the%20procedural%20mandate%20and%20the%20defence%E2%80%99s%20claim%20that%20the%20papers%20were%20intentionally%20kept%20in%20loose%20paper%20form%20so%20as%20to%20replace%20them%20to%20suit%20the%20police%E2%80%99s%20story%20was%20accepted%20by%20the%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilar%20questions%20were%20also%20raised%20about%20the%20police%E2%80%99s%20claim%20around%20Rahi%20and%20Vijay%20Tikri%E2%80%99s%20arrests%20and%20%E2%80%9Cincriminating%20documents%E2%80%9D%20seized%20from%20them.%20According%20to%20the%20police%2C%20Rahi%2C%20a%20journalist%2C%20and%20Tikri%20were%20taken%20into%20custody%20from%20one%20Chichgarh%20T-point%20on%20the%20evening%20of%20September%201%2C%202013.%20The%20arrest%20panchnamas%2C%20however%2C%20don%E2%80%99t%20mention%20the%20time.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20evidence%20allegedly%20recovered%20from%20them%20was%20seized%20only%20a%20day%20later.%20This%20The%20court%20has%20blamed%20Bawche%20for%20not%20providing%20any%20clarity%20and%20for%20keeping%20the%20documents%20ambiguous.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20Saibaba%20was%20arrested%20on%20May%209%2C%202014%2C%20his%20house%20in%20Delhi%20was%20raided%20almost%20seven%20months%20before%20that%2C%20on%20September%2012%2C%202013.%20Bawche%20in%20his%20testimony%20before%20the%20trial%20court%2C%20had%20claimed%20that%20when%20they%20had%20tried%20to%20arrest%20Saibaba%2C%20his%20%E2%80%9Cparty%20members%E2%80%9D%20had%20tried%20to%20create%20a%20%E2%80%9Claw%20and%20order%E2%80%9D%20situation%20in%20the%20capital%20city.%20The%20high%20court%20rubbished%20these%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBawche%20continues%20to%20be%20celebrated%20for%20leading%20many%20investigations%20in%20the%20Gadchiroli%20region.%20After%20a%20%E2%80%9Csuccessful%20conviction%E2%80%9D%20in%20Saibaba%E2%80%99s%20case%2C%20then%20chief%20minister%20Devendra%20Fadnavis%20had%20publicly%20applauded%20him%20for%20his%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBawche%2C%20now%20a%20Deputy%20Commissioner%20of%20Police%20(DCP)%20in%20Mumbai%2C%20however%2C%20is%20not%20new%20to%20controversy.%20In%202017%2C%20when%20human%20rights%20advocate%20Surendra%20Gadling%20was%20representing%20Saibaba%20in%20the%20case%2C%20he%20was%20allegedly%20threatened%20by%20Bawche%20of%20dire%20consequences%20right%20inside%20the%20court.%20According%20to%20an%20affidavit%20submitted%20by%20Gadling%E2%80%99s%20then%20junior%20advocate%20Jagdish%20Meshram%2C%20Bawche%20after%20his%20deposition%20in%20the%20Gadchiroli%20court%2C%20had%20told%20Gadling%20%E2%80%9Cafter%20Saibaba%2C%20it%20is%20your%20turn%20to%20go%20to%20jail%E2%80%9D.%20Meshram%E2%80%99s%20affidavit%20also%20mentions%20names%20of%20other%20lawyers%20who%20were%20present%20at%20that%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20allegation%20makes%20sense%20when%20seen%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20arrests%20made%20in%20the%20Elgar%20Parishad%20case%20in%202018.%20Although%20Bawche%20did%20not%20have%20any%20direct%20role%20in%20the%20investigation%2C%20he%20was%20present%20at%20the%20times%20of%20raids%20and%20arrests%20that%20were%20carried%20out%20across%20India%20in%202018.%20Bawche%20had%20led%20the%20raid%20at%20Gadling%E2%80%99s%20residence%20in%20Nagpur.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20initial%20chargesheet%20filed%20by%20the%20Pune%20police%20has%20mention%20of%20letters%20sent%20by%20Bawche%20to%20different%20state%20police%20before%20the%20raids%20carried%20out%20at%20Telugu%20poet%20Varavara%20Roa%E2%80%99s%20residence%20in%20Hyderabad%20and%20academic%20and%20lawyer%20Sudha%20Bharadwaj%E2%80%99s%20residence%20in%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20defence%20lawyers%20recall%20Bawche%E2%80%99s%20presence%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20at%20the%20time%20of%20the%20hearing%20in%20historian%20Romila%20Thapar%E2%80%99s%20petition%20against%20the%20first%20round%20of%20arrests%20made%20in%20the%20Elgar%20Parishad%20case%20in%202018.%20Later%2C%20in%202019%2C%20when%20the%20Fadnavis-led%20BJP%20government%20fell%20in%20Mahrashtra%20and%20the%20Mahavikas%20Aghadi%20government%20took%20charge%2C%20a%20delegation%20of%20human%20rights%20activists%20and%20lawyers%20had%20visited%20Ajit%20Pawar%2C%20the%20then%20deputy%20chief%20minister.%20Here%20too%2C%20Bawche%20was%20present%20to%20apprise%20the%20state%20about%20the%20goings-on%20in%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710311451000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F13111914%2FBKzOcnek_400x400.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fio-whose-role-bombay-hc-questioned-in-saibaba-case-was-also-part-of-elgar-parishad-probe%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Pune%20police%2C%20at%20multiple%20places%20in%20the%20Elgar%20Parishad%20chargesheet%2C%20claimed%20that%20some%20of%20those%20arrested%20in%20the%20Elgar%20Parishad%20case%20had%20a%20%E2%80%9Cdirect%20association%E2%80%9D%20with%20Saibaba.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fio-whose-role-bombay-hc-questioned-in-saibaba-case-was-also-part-of-elgar-parishad-probe%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Russia%20fully%20prepared%20for%20nuclear%20war%20if%20threatened%3A%20Putin%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710310642000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-108454891%2Cimgsize-781426.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fw