na-reveals%5C%22%3Emost%20Indians%20are%20a%20mixture%20of%20three%20ancestral%20populations%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20hunter-gatherers%20who%20lived%20in%20the%20region%20for%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20years%2C%20farmers%20with%20Iranian%20ancestry%20who%20arrived%20between%204700%20and%203000%20B.C.E.%20and%20herders%20from%20the%20central%20Eurasian%20steppe%20region%20who%20came%20sometime%20after%203000%20B.C.E.%2C%20perhaps%20between%201900%20and%201500%20B.C.E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20the%20scientists%20found%20that%20modern%20individuals%20sampled%20derive%201%25%20to%202%25%20of%20their%20ancestry%20from%20Neanderthals%20and%20their%20close%20cousins%2C%20the%20Denisovans%20which%20is%20on%20par%20with%20Europeans%20and%20Indians%20collectively%20carry%20a%20stunning%20variety%20of%20these%20archaic%20genes%20compared%20with%20other%20worldwide%20populations%2C%20%3Cem%3EScience%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20this%20study%20%E2%80%94%20assumed%20to%20be%20the%20largest%20ever%20modern%20whole-genome%20analysis%20from%20South%20Asia%2C%20published%20as%20a%20preprint%20last%20month%20on%20bioRxiv%20%E2%80%94%20about%2090%25%20of%20all%20known%20Neanderthal%20genes%20that%20have%20made%20their%20way%20into%20human%20populations%20turned%20up%20in%20the%202700%20Indian%20genomes.%20It%20is%20about%2050%25%20more%20than%20what%20was%20recovered%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Farticles%2Fs41586-020-2225-9%5C%22%3Ea%20similar%20study%20of%20Neanderthal%20DNA%20in%20Icelanders%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20analysed%20more%20than%2027%2C000%20genomes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoorjani%20speculated%20that%20%E2%80%9Cancient%20humans%20might%20have%20encountered%20and%20mated%20with%20a%20relatively%20large%2C%20genetically%20diverse%20population%20of%20our%20archaic%20cousins%20living%20on%20the%20subcontinent%20%E2%80%94%20although%20no%20fossils%20of%20those%20archaic%20cousins%20have%20been%20found%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Cem%3EScience%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%20According%20to%20another%20assumption%20by%20scientists%2C%20there%20is%20a%20possibility%20that%20different%20segments%20of%20Neanderthal%20DNA%20is%20preserved%20better%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20vast%20geography%20and%20close%20kin-marrying%20traditions%20compared%20to%20other%20places.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTo%20find%20out%20more%20about%20the%20identity%20of%20the%20Iranian-related%20farmers%20who%20entered%20the%20region%20thousands%20of%20years%20ago%2C%20the%20researchers%20analyzed%20previously%20extracted%20ancient%20DNA%20from%20groups%20with%20Iranian%20ancestry%20who%20predated%20the%20genetic%20pulse%20into%20India.%20They%20then%20played%20out%20simulations%20to%20see%20whose%20genes%20best%20matched%20the%20patterns%20seen%20in%20present-day%20Indians.%20The%20best%20fit%20came%20from%20farmers%20from%20an%20ancient%20agricultural%20center%20called%20Sarazm%20in%20the%20northwest%20of%20what%20today%20is%20Tajikistan.%20Farmers%20here%20grew%20wheat%20and%20barley%20and%20kept%20cattle%2C%20and%20traded%20extensively%20throughout%20Eurasia%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Cem%3EScience%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPopulation%20geneticist%20Kelsey%20Witt%20of%20Clemson%20University%20told%20%3Cem%3EScience%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20this%20research%20was%20important%20as%20India%20had%20largely%20been%20ignored%20in%20global%20population%20geneticist%20Kelsey%20Witt%20of%20Clemson%20University.%20%E2%80%9CWe%E2%80%99re%20learning%20a%20lot%20about%20populations%20that%20we%20didn%E2%80%99t%20know%20much%20about%2C%E2%80%9D%20Witt%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710302606000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F13093230%2Fkarthik-chandran-uwSbfD1afxI-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fscience%2Fnew-study-sheds-light-on-where-indias-people-came-from%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20study%20carried%20out%20by%20University%20of%20California%2C%2